Read data in spark | Lec-3 | Read modes in spark

# PYSPARK DATAFRAME READER – SHORT NOTES

---

## 1. CORE SYNTAX
spark.read \
  .format("file_type") \
  .option("key", "value") \
  .schema(defined_schema) \
  .load("path")

---

## 2. FORMAT (5 TYPES)
- CSV   → spark.read.csv("path")
- JSON  → spark.read.json("path")
- Parquet → spark.read.parquet("path")
- JDBC  → spark.read.jdbc(url, table)
- Table → spark.sql("SELECT * FROM table")

---

## 3. COMMON OPTIONS
- .option("header", "true")        → first row as column names
- .option("inferSchema", "true")   → auto-detect data types
- .option("mode", "PERMISSIVE")    → error handling (see below)

---

## 4. MODE OPTIONS
- PERMISSIVE     → set NULL for bad fields (default)
- DROPMALFORMED  → skip bad rows
- FAILFAST       → stop execution on error

---

## 5. MANUAL SCHEMA (Optional)
from pyspark.sql.types import *
schema = StructType([StructField("id", IntegerType(), True), ...])
spark.read.schema(schema).csv("path")

---

## 6. PRACTICAL EXAMPLE (Flight Data)
flight_df = (spark.read.format("csv")
    .option("header", "true")
    .option("inferSchema", "true")
    .option("mode", "FAILFAST")
    .load("/FileStore/tables/flight_data.csv"))
flight_df.show(5)

---

## 7. KEY TAKEAWAYS
- spark.read = entry point
- format() → file type
- option() → config
- schema() → manual type safety
- load() → file path

✅ Best Practice: use header=true & inferSchema=true for CSV.


